[The removal of mandatory vaccination for schoolchildren is a dangerous step backwards. It reflects the growing vaccine hesitancy prevalent in many countries, as well as a distrust of institutions and of science. Measles tripled in Europe in 2017, ECDC reports: 30 European nations reported a total of 14 451 measles cases in 2017, more than 3 times the number reported in 2016 with 4643 reported cases. WHO estimates that more than 450 children die each day from measles, making it a leading cause of death. Measles is a vaccine-preventable disease with an outstanding safety record. It is the best and least expensive way to prevent the disease and protect the population at risk. - Mod.LK

HealthMap, Italy: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5961680,75.]
